City.CityDescrition: No one knows where Gas Stations #1 through #65 are, but the proprietors insist on keeping the name.

No one is sure what the acronym means. All that is known is that after the Fall, the first people who came here found it on a sign by the entrance, thus giving the city its name. Due to its proximity to the nearby BD City, the two cities are major trading partners.

No one is sure what the acronym means. All that is known is that after the Fall, the first people who came here found it on a sign by the entrance, thus giving the city its name. Due to its proximity to the nearby SM City, the two cities are major trading partners.

A gas station located in the middle of the Dustlands, looking out over the Dead Center, the central plague zone. Many adventurers stop off here on their way to explore the Dead Center. Few ever make it back again.

TriggerList.Name: 安全城市_亡灵谷加油站

City.CityDescrition: This gas station stands at the entrance to the far north, serving entrepreneurs hoping to find riches in Wraith Valley.
Built in the middle of a basin, Sanctuary's fertile agricultural land attracts large amounts of settlers despite its inconvenient location.
This lookout keeps watch over the north to ensure the safety of the city of Metropol.
A lookout located in the middle of a canyon, where cold northern winds blow all year round.
This lookout watches for infected hordes coming from the south.
This town takes its name from a pre-Fall oil well, which continues to produce small amounts of crude oil to this day.
Named for a small, naturally occurring oil well, this city is much smaller than its grandiose name might suggest, and its location on the edge of the Dustlands means that few ever visit.
A town built by film fanatics. Its name is said to have been inspired by a pre-Fall settlement.

This rest stop is located on a barren and otherwise unremarkable stretch of land nestled between the mountains. However, due to its position on the route from Metropol to the hinterlands, it sees plenty of people passing through.
A gas station located at the entrance to the southern desert.
A small town located in a narrow gorge leading from the central plains to the western mountains. The gorge is also the only way to reach Metropol.
A gas station located in the center of the foothills.
A lookout located in the foothills of the frontier, looking out over the endless snow-capped mountains. No one's crossed them since the days of the Pre-Fallers.
An entirely unremarkable gas station.
An entirely unremarkable village.

TriggerList.Name: 安全城市_废土银行（亡灵山分行）

City.CityDescrition: A less-than-legitimate organization offering savings, loans, and wealth management services.

TriggerList.Name: 安全城市_废土银行（小岔岭分行）

City.CityDescrition: A less-than-legitimate organization offering savings, loans, and wealth management services.

TriggerList.Name: 安全城市_废土银行（远霞分行）

City.CityDescrition: A less-than-legitimate organization offering savings, loans, and wealth management services.
This gas station is said to have a large supply of scrapped truck parts in stock.
A small village built by farmers.
No one knows where this city's name came from. It is said to have been written on the door of a pre-Fall building located in the middle of the city—nobody knows what the building was for, either.

A small village located in the desert hinterlands. Its inhabitants eke a living out of the nearby oasis. Many explorers planning to venture deeper into the infected cities of the desert will stop by here for a spell.
A gas station located far to the north. It's pretty chilly up here.
This is the westernmost gas station on the map. Keep going west from here, and you'll find absolutely nothing.
A gas station located within the swampy wetlands.
A rest stop located in the middle of a swamp, serving the fugitives who try to make their way across.
A private residence located deep within the mountains. Its owner is rarely seen, preferring to trade with the outside world through their household staff.
A private residence. Within its courtyard is a pond where people are sometimes seen fishing.
This gas station offers shelter for passing truckers. Its name comes from the crowd of fortune-telling old ladies who ply their trade here.

A city built in the middle of the wetlands. It's said to have begun as an attempt to fend off infected hordes by building simple fortifications from mud, before growing into the city that stands today.
A village in the middle of the wetlands.
The only rest stop in the vast desert on the way to Civitas.
This town was once famous for producing various types of ore, but it has since fallen into decline, with only a handful of farmers remaining.
A sentry post serving as Civitas' first line of defense against infected hordes coming from the southwest. That being said, many years have passed without a single incident.

A city formed by a conglomerate of criminal enterprises. Though Civitas has a perfectly functional economic and political system, its main source of income is derived from shaking down neighboring settlements for protection money. For this purpose, the city leadership employs a substantial workforce of thugs, goons, and general ne'er-do-wells.
In the middle of this town lies a small pond lush seemingly connected to an aquifer. The pond, lush with reeds, is probably the most interesting thing about the place.
Famous for producing apples, this town's remote location means that its ageing inhabitants see little in the way of young, fresh faces.
Every house near this rest stop is filled with blue furniture. No one knows why.
Located to the west of the central plains, this gas station is a popular rest stop among truckers headed for the western hills.
A large city in the central Dustlands. A lawful place with abundant resources and well-built amenities.
Located at the very edge of the Dustlands, to the south of this rest stop lies endless desert. What lies beyond that? Only the Pre-Fallers know for sure.

TriggerList.Name: 安全城市_道路建设局（凌春山分局）

City.CityDescrition: An organization dedicated to the construction of roads.

TriggerList.Name: 安全城市_道路建设总局

City.CityDescrition: An organization dedicated to the construction of roads.

A town located in the narrow pass through the western mountains—the only path to the central plains. People say that the hordes of infected that invaded from the west ten years ago began their destructive rampage here.

A large city located in the middle of the Dustlands. Some say it stood here long before society fell to pieces. After the Fall, military peacekeeping forces garrisoned the city and built defenses here, preparing for an onslaught by infected hordes. Now, the city is run by a democratically elected government.
An ordinary farming village. It's said that the people here use the infected as a means of divination... which sounds hard to believe.

In the earliest days following the Fall, no part of the Dustlands could be considered as having a unified leadership. But as its largest city, Metropol was referred to as the "capital of the Dustlands," perhaps solely out of a desire to maintain some sense of order. Due to its abundant natural resources, the city of Metropol is awash with scrap and building materials, serving as a trading center for all the Dustlands' major cities. Due to its huge resource needs, goods are scarce here—but it's a good place for sellers to make a quick buck.
A town located on a major thoroughfare. All sorts of people pass through here—both upstanding citizens and less reputable types.

A small town in the middle of the central plains, with fertile soil suitable for farming. But due to its proximity to a number of major cities, most of its young people have moved away, leaving only the old-timers behind.
A rest stop located in the middle of the mountains. If you're not crossing the mountains, it's hard to imagine why you'd want to visit.
A small farm, named after its bucktoothed owner. Recently, they've built a textiles workshop here in the hopes of getting into the clothing business...
A small gas station, named after its bucktoothed owner.

TradeCity.CityDescrition: This gas station is said to have a large supply of scrapped truck parts in stock.
A small town located in a narrow gorge leading from the central plains to the western mountains. The gorge is also the only way to reach Metropol.

This rest stop is located on a barren and otherwise unremarkable stretch of land nestled between the mountains. However, due to its position on the route from Metropol to the hinterlands, it sees plenty of people passing through.
This town was once famous for producing various types of ore, but it has since fallen into decline, with only a handful of farmers remaining.
An organization dedicated to the construction of roads.
Located to the west of the central plains, this gas station is a popular rest stop among truckers headed for the western hills.

A town located in the narrow pass through the western mountains—the only path to the central plains. People say that the hordes of infected that invaded from the west ten years ago began their destructive rampage here.
A gas station located at the entrance to the southern desert.

A large city located in the middle of the Dustlands. Some say it stood here long before society fell to pieces. After the Fall, military peacekeeping forces garrisoned the city and built defenses here, preparing for an onslaught by infected hordes. Now, the city is run by a democratically elected government.

A small town in the middle of the central plains, with fertile soil suitable for farming. But due to its proximity to a number of major cities, most of its young people have moved away, leaving only the old-timers behind.
This town takes its name from a pre-Fall oil well, which continues to produce small amounts of crude oil to this day.
The only rest stop in the vast desert on the way to Civitas.
Located to the west of the central plains, this gas station is a popular rest stop among truckers headed for the western hills.
A rest stop located in the middle of a swamp, serving the fugitives who try to make their way across.

No one is sure what the acronym means. All that is known is that after the Fall, the first people who came here found it on a sign by the entrance, thus giving the city its name. Due to its proximity to the nearby BD City, the two cities are major trading partners.
Named for a small, naturally occurring oil well, this city is much smaller than its grandiose name might suggest, and its location on the edge of the Dustlands means that few ever visit.

No one is sure what the acronym means. All that is known is that after the Fall, the first people who came here found it on a sign by the entrance, thus giving the city its name. Due to its proximity to the nearby SM City, the two cities are major trading partners.
A rest stop located in the middle of the mountains. If you're not crossing the mountains, it's hard to imagine why you'd want to visit.
A town located on a major thoroughfare. All sorts of people pass through here—both upstanding citizens and less reputable types.
An organization dedicated to the construction of roads.

A city built in the middle of the wetlands. It's said to have begun as an attempt to fend off infected hordes by building simple fortifications from mud, before growing into the city that stands today.
A gas station located within the swampy wetlands.
An entirely unremarkable village.
A less-than-legitimate organization offering savings, loans, and wealth management services.
A gas station located in the center of the foothills.
An organization dedicated to the construction of roads.
Famous for producing apples, this town's remote location means that its ageing inhabitants see little in the way of young, fresh faces.
